tldr: The user requested a review of a sleep questionnaire application against
  its acceptance criteria and the implementation of missing features. The agent
  successfully added a tiredness severity scale, COMISA and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome detection, weighted EDS scoring, expanded CSV export, and
  pain/chronic fatigue screening, along with external resource links.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to ensure all acceptance criteria from the Statement of
  Work and detailed specification were met, and to implement any identified
  gaps. The agent conducted a thorough analysis, identifying several missing
  features. Subsequently, the agent systematically implemented these features.
  Key additions included a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with
  safety warnings for high scores, and the integration of detection logic for
  complex sleep disorders like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. The agent
  also enhanced the reporting by incorporating weighted scoring for Excessive
  Daytime Sleepiness and adding a dedicated section for external sleep and
  mental health resources. Furthermore, the CSV export was significantly
  improved to include all questionnaire data, and new questions were introduced
  to screen for pain affecting sleep and chronic fatigue symptoms. The
  implementation involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI
  components, and both web and PDF report generation logic, ensuring a more
  robust and informative application.
